To install Argo CD in a Kubernetes cluster, follow these steps:

Prerequisites:
 A running Kubernetes cluster (e.g., Minikube, EKS, AKS, GKE, etc.)
kubectl installed and configured to access the cluster
Optional: argocd CLI tool installed (for easier interaction)

---

Step-by-Step Installation

1. Install Argo CD in the argocd namespace


kubectl create namespace argocd
kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml


This deploys all necessary Argo CD components (API server, controller, repo-server, etc.).

---

2. Expose the Argo CD API server

Option 1: Port-forward (for testing/local use)


kubectl port-forward svc/argocd-server -n argocd 8080:443
```

Now Argo CD is available at:  
https://localhost:8080

Option 2: LoadBalancer or Ingress (for production)
You can patch the service to expose it via LoadBalancer:


kubectl patch svc argocd-server -n argocd -p '{"spec": {"type": "LoadBalancer"}}'
```

---

 3. Get the initial admin password


kubectl get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -n argocd -o jsonpath="{.data.password}" | base64 -d
```

Username: admin 
Password: *(value from above command)*



4. (Optional) Install argocd CLI

macOS (brew)
brew install argocd

Linux
sudo curl -sSL -o /usr/local/bin/argocd https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd/releases/latest/download/argocd-linux-amd64
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/argocd


Verify:

argocd version


---

5. Login to Argo CD using CLI


argocd login localhost:8080 --username admin --password <your-password> --insecure


(Use the IP/domain of your server if exposed externally.)

---

